Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.08,0:02:43.01,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Coming home from Vietnam was
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.18,0:02:46.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,close to as traumatic as the war itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.08,0:02:50.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,For years, nobody talked about Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.74,0:02:56.14,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We were friends with a young couple
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.44,0:03:00.44,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and it was only after 12 years that the two wives were talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.64,0:03:03.65,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Found out that we both had been Marines in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.03,0:03:06.37,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Never said a word about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.37,0:03:08.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Never mentioned it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.40,0:03:11.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And the whole country was like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.76,0:03:14.25,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It was so divisive.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.55,0:03:19.34,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And it's like living in a family with an alcoholic father.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.45,0:03:22.55,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"Shh, we don't talk about that."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.67,0:03:26.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Our country did that with Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.47,0:03:29.33,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It's only been very recently that, I think, that,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.35,0:03:32.01,英文对白,,0,0,0,,you know, the baby boomers are finally starting to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.03,0:03:33.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.03,0:03:35.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,What happened?"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.51,0:03:46.70,英文对白,,0,0,0,,What we need now in this country
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.25,0:03:49.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,is to heal the wounds
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.29,0:03:51.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and to put Vietnam behind us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.55,0:04:06.86,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The killing in this tragic war must stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.86,0:04:19.92,英文对白,,0,0,0,,General Westmoreland's strategy
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.93,0:04:21.70,英文对白,,0,0,0,,is producing results.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.35,0:04:25.88,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The enemy is no longer closer to victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.53,0:04:34.88,英文对白,,0,0,0,,No matter how you measure it,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.90,0:04:38.51,英文对白,,0,0,0,,we're better off than we thought we would be at this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.07,0:04:46.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,You have been less than candid
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.07,0:04:50.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as to how deeply we are involved in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.19,0:04:52.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We have increased our assistance
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.05,0:04:54.14,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to the government, its logistics.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.15,0:04:56.17,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We have not sent combat troops there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.59,0:04:59.84,英文对白,,0,0,0,,You have a row of dominoes set up
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.86,0:05:02.58,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and you knock over the first one and the last one,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.59,0:05:03.98,英文对白,,0,0,0,,certainly it will go over.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.00,0:05:06.12,英文对白,,0,0,0,,If aggression is successful in Korea,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.14,0:05:09.34,英文对白,,0,0,0,,we can expect it to spread throughout Asia and Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.36,0:05:10.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and to this hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.08,0:05:49.58,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Viktor Frankl, who survived the death camps in World War II,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.63,0:05:52.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,wrote a book called Man's Search for Meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.90,0:05:57.27,英文对白,,0,0,0,,You know, "To live is to suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.87,0:06:00.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,To survive is to find meaning in suffering."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.51,0:06:06.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And for those of us who suffered because of Vietnam,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.52,0:06:10.96,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that's been our quest ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.24,0:06:28.30,英文对白,,0,0,0,,America's involvement in Vietnam began in secrecy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.78,0:06:33.42,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It ended, 30 years later, in failure,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.43,0:06:36.27,英文对白,,0,0,0,,witnessed by the entire world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.73,0:06:42.98,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It was begun in good faith by decent people
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.00,0:06:45.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,out of fateful misunderstandings,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.66,0:06:50.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,American overconfidence, and Cold War miscalculation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.25,0:06:52.67,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And it was prolonged
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.67,0:06:55.42,英文对白,,0,0,0,,because it seemed easier to muddle through
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.44,0:06:59.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,than admit that it had been caused by tragic decisions,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.52,0:07:02.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,made by five American presidents,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.07,0:07:05.32,英文对白,,0,0,0,,belonging to both political parties.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.09,0:07:08.71,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Before the war was over,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.73,0:07:12.48,英文对白,,0,0,0,,more than 58,000 Americans would be dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.37,0:07:17.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,At least 250,000 South Vietnamese troops
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.39,0:07:19.75,英文对白,,0,0,0,,died in the conflict, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.84,0:07:24.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,So did over a million North Vietnamese soldiers
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.20,0:07:26.33,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and Viet Cong guerrillas.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.35,0:07:34.21,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Two million civilians, north and south,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.22,0:07:35.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,are thought to have perished,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.91,0:07:38.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as well as tens of thousands more
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.36,0:07:42.02,英文对白,,0,0,0,,in the neighboring states of Laos and Cambodia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.08,0:07:45.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,For many Vietnamese,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.77,0:07:47.81,英文对白,,0,0,0,,it was a brutal civil war;
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.56,0:07:51.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,for others, the bloody climactic chapter
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.70,0:07:54.96,英文对白,,0,0,0,,in a century-old struggle for independence.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.69,0:08:02.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,For those Americans who fought in it,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.92,0:08:05.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and for those who fought against it back home,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.80,0:08:09.88,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as well as for those who merely glimpsed it on the nightly news,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.21,0:08:13.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the Vietnam War was a decade of agony,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.27,0:08:18.14,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the most divisive period since the Civil War.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.22,0:08:23.90,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Vietnam seemed to call everything into question...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.06,0:08:27.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the value of honor and gallantry;
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.44,0:08:32.37,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the qualities of cruelty and mercy;
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.24,0:08:36.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the candor of the American government;
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.06,0:08:41.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and what it means to be a patriot.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.44,0:08:50.34,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And those who lived through it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.36,0:08:52.92,英文对白,,0,0,0,,have never been able to erase its memory,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.18,0:08:56.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,have never stopped arguing about what really happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.74,0:08:59.66,英文对白,,0,0,0,,why everything went so badly wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.74,0:09:01.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,who was to blame,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.24,0:09:04.49,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and whether it was all worth it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.18,0:10:45.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The French conquest of Indochina began with
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.14,0:10:50.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,an attack on the ancient Vietnamese port of Danang in 1858.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.34,0:10:55.00,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It took 50 years to lay claim to the whole region...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.01,0:10:56.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Laos and Cambodia,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.69,0:10:59.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as well as the 1,200-mile-long area
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.95,0:11:02.44,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that would come to be called Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.78,0:11:08.92,英文对白,,0,0,0,,All of it was ruled by a French governor-general
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.93,0:11:10.88,英文对白,,0,0,0,,from his palace in Hanoi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.48,0:11:16.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The French largely lived on plantation estates,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.41,0:11:18.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and in cities, like Saigon,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.58,0:11:22.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,made to look as much as possible like those at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.20,0:11:27.01,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Most did not even bother to learn the language
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.02,0:11:28.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,spoken by their subjects.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.75,0:11:33.36,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Instead they installed a series of puppet emperors
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.37,0:11:37.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and employed a network of French-speaking Vietnamese officials...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.53,0:11:38.61,英文对白,,0,0,0,,mandarins...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.62,0:11:41.15,英文对白,,0,0,0,,willing to carry out their wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.81,0:11:46.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The French put their subjects to work
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.39,0:11:48.81,英文对白,,0,0,0,,building roads and canals,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.82,0:11:51.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,railroads and bridges.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.11,0:12:11.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The Vietnamese people did not take easily to French occupation,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.58,0:12:16.21,英文对白,,0,0,0,,just as they had fought against earlier invasions by the Chinese.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.30,0:12:20.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,By the early 20th century, nationalism was on the rise.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.00,0:12:24.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But anyone who dared resist colonial rule
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.12,0:12:28.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,risked exile, prison, or the guillotine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.27,0:13:24.73,英文对白,,0,0,0,,My hatred for them was pure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.03,0:13:27.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Pure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.61,0:13:29.37,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I hated them so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.85,0:13:32.11,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And I was so scared of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.29,0:13:38.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Boy, I was terrified of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.22,0:13:49.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And the scareder I got, the more I hated them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.93,0:13:55.61,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I was an 18-year-old Marine rifleman
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.64,0:13:58.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,with the ink still wet on my high school diploma.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.93,0:14:01.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to shame myself in front of my buddies.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.15,0:14:04.74,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But I was so scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.38,0:14:08.28,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I felt like I was hanging onto my honor by my fingernails
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.29,0:14:09.78,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the whole time I was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.68,0:14:26.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In the Spring of 1919,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.90,0:14:30.22,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as the victorious Allied Powers met in Paris
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.23,0:14:33.41,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to rebuild a world shattered by the Great War,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.08,0:14:37.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,President Woodrow Wilson headed the American delegation
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.94,0:14:40.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,housed in the Hotel Crillon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.56,0:14:46.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,One day, a tall, slender, 29-year-old man
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.65,0:14:49.22,英文对白,,0,0,0,,appeared with a petition for the president
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.23,0:14:52.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,he and other Vietnamese nationalists had written.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.27,0:14:56.70,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Inspired by Wilson's declaration
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.71,0:14:59.85,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that the interests of colonial peoples should be given
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.86,0:15:03.25,英文对白,,0,0,0,,equal weight with those of their European rulers,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.44,0:15:08.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the man was asking that this principle be applied to his homeland.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.44,0:15:12.99,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The president's secretary promised to show it to Wilson,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.20,0:15:16.14,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but there is no evidence that he ever did.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.86,0:15:19.44,英文对白,,0,0,0,,His name was Nguyen Tat Thanh,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.46,0:15:23.75,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but he was now living under an alias, Nguyen Ai Quoc...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.08,0:15:25.92,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"Nguyen the Patriot."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.57,0:15:29.65,英文对白,,0,0,0,,During his long, shadowy career,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.67,0:15:33.30,英文对白,,0,0,0,,he would adopt some 70 different pseudonyms,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.60,0:15:37.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,finally settling on "the most enlightened one"...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.86,0:15:39.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.90,0:15:43.00,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh was a man who
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.02,0:15:46.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,succeeded in projecting an image of somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.20,0:15:51.53,英文对白,,0,0,0,,who was totally dedicated to freeing his country and his people
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.54,0:15:53.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,from foreign domination
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.78,0:15:59.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to the point that he sacrificed his own well-being, his own life,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.40,0:16:02.37,英文对白,,0,0,0,,not having a family of his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.56,0:16:06.11,英文对白,,0,0,0,,To Vietnamese, that's a big sacrifice
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.12,0:16:09.45,英文对白,,0,0,0,,because to us everybody needs a family.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.67,0:16:13.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh was born in 1890,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.40,0:16:16.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the son of a minor official in the French regime.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.45,0:16:21.25,英文对白,,0,0,0,,After taking part in a demonstration against the puppet emperor
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.26,0:16:23.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and the Frenchmen who pulled his strings,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.88,0:16:27.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho was expelled from school and marked for arrest.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.26,0:16:35.15,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He left Vietnam in 1911 and remained in exile for 30 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.54,0:16:39.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He served as a cook's helper aboard a French liner,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.78,0:16:42.54,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and visited New York and Boston,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.55,0:16:46.79,英文对白,,0,0,0,,where he worked for a time as a pastry chef at the Parker House.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.77,0:16:50.12,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He shoveled snow in London,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.61,0:16:53.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,tinted photographs in Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.56,0:16:58.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,There, Ho Chi Minh joined the French Socialist Party.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.49,0:17:02.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But when he discovered the anti-colonial writings of Lenin,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.25,0:17:03.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,he became a communist.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.35,0:17:07.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He was invited to Moscow to study,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.91,0:17:10.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,underwent training as a Soviet agent,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.53,0:17:14.45,英文对白,,0,0,0,,was sometimes criticized for being a nationalist first,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.47,0:17:16.02,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a communist second,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.90,0:17:18.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and then was dispatched to China
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.99,0:17:22.51,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to organize a cell of other Vietnamese exiles
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.52,0:17:26.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and help establish the Indochinese Communist Party.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.18,0:17:29.27,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Through it all,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.27,0:17:31.15,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"He was taut and quivering,"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.16,0:17:32.27,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a friend remembered,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.27,0:17:33.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"with only one thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.40,0:17:36.88,英文对白,,0,0,0,,his country, Vietnam."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.35,0:17:56.63,英文对白,,0,0,0,,By 1940, much of the world was at war again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.63,0:18:07.84,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Germany had seized most of Western Europe,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.17,0:18:09.86,英文对白,,0,0,0,,including France.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.04,0:18:14.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Imperial Japan threatened
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.95,0:18:17.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,many of the European colonies in Asia,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.48,0:18:19.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and occupied Vietnam,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.47,0:18:23.27,英文对白,,0,0,0,,where they permitted their allies, the collaborationist French,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.30,0:18:25.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to continue to oversee their colony.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.30,0:18:30.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,To some Vietnamese,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.91,0:18:33.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the coming of the Japanese seemed to signal
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.59,0:18:36.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a welcome end to white colonial rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.56,0:18:40.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But Ho Chi Minh, still in exile in China,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.79,0:18:43.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,saw the Japanese as alien invaders,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.81,0:18:45.90,英文对白,,0,0,0,,no more welcome than the French.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.82,0:18:49.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They were only interested in exploiting his country
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.98,0:18:54.53,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and seizing Vietnamese crops to fill their own rice bowls.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.37,0:18:58.01,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The time had come, he said,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.02,0:19:01.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to rally "patriots of all ages and all types,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.75,0:19:05.50,英文对白,,0,0,0,,peasants, workers, merchants and soldiers"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.51,0:19:09.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to defeat the Japanese and the collaborationist French.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.35,0:19:15.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In February of 1941,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.89,0:19:18.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,after three decades away from his homeland,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.65,0:19:23.25,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh slipped back across the Chinese border into Vietnam
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.27,0:19:27.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and set up headquarters near the remote village of Pac Bo
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.47,0:19:30.51,英文对白,,0,0,0,,in a limestone cave at the side of a mountain
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.52,0:19:33.00,英文对白,,0,0,0,,he named for Karl Marx,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.56,0:19:37.65,英文对白,,0,0,0,,overlooking a jungle stream he named for his hero,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.66,0:19:38.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Lenin.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.67,0:19:43.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,There, he founded a revolutionary movement,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.60,0:19:47.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,which he called the Vietnam Independence League...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.50,0:19:48.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the Viet Minh.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.70,0:20:06.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,To build and lead a fighting force for his revolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.05,0:20:08.75,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho called upon Vo Nguyen Giap,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.76,0:20:11.33,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a one-time teacher of French history
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.34,0:20:14.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,who had instructed the children of Hanoi's elite.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.86,0:20:18.58,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Giap was an early convert to communism,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.60,0:20:22.00,英文对白,,0,0,0,,whose life-long hatred for the French intensified
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.01,0:20:25.02,英文对白,,0,0,0,,when they beat his wife to death in prison.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.67,0:20:29.96,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Inspired by Napoleon, Lawrence of Arabia,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.97,0:20:33.53,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and the communist Chinese revolutionary Mao Zedong,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.54,0:20:38.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Giap had already begun to develop a distinctive theory of warfare
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.38,0:20:40.84,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that relied on guerrilla tactics
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.05,0:20:45.25,英文对白,,0,0,0,,until a full-scale conventional attack could be mounted.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.26,0:20:49.70,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In the fight for independence which he believed was coming,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.91,0:20:55.75,英文对白,,0,0,0,,his armies, Giap said, would be "everywhere and nowhere."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.45,0:21:00.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The reason Vietnamese had always resort to guerrilla warfare
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.48,0:21:02.78,英文对白,,0,0,0,,was because we were a small country.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.80,0:21:07.15,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And it was just a way of fight the weak against the strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.73,0:21:12.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Don't fight unless you're sure you can win,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.17,0:21:15.88,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and surprise is a big element.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.49,0:21:19.15,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Choose your own battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.33,0:21:29.78,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I had about 26 guys that day out of 45.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.79,0:21:32.08,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We were always somewhat understrength.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.09,0:21:34.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And this day we were quite understrength.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.23,0:21:38.36,英文对白,,0,0,0,,My platoon's on point.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.18,0:21:44.79,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Go, go, go, go, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.80,0:21:47.73,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And all of a sudden the very point man,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.75,0:21:49.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the first guy in the column,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.53,0:21:52.88,英文对白,,0,0,0,,said, "VC on the trail. VC on the trail."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.70,0:21:57.44,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Before I had a chance to digest this...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.60,0:21:59.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,... he went down, shot right through the chest.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.82,0:22:05.85,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And what was a very well-laid ambush erupted.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.17,0:22:18.98,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I knew I'd lost a bunch of guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.99,0:22:20.99,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I said a prayer to God
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.44,0:22:22.41,英文对白,,0,0,0,,saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.83,0:22:25.54,英文对白,,0,0,0,,basically, "If you need any more guys from my platoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.55,0:22:27.71,英文对白,,0,0,0,,take me. Don't take any more of my men."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.04,0:22:29.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,As soon as I said it,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.94,0:22:31.41,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I freaked myself out and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.43,0:22:34.75,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"Holy shit. Can I take that prayer back?"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.80,0:22:49.21,英文对白,,0,0,0,,By the Spring of 1945,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.84,0:22:53.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,more than three years after the Japanese attack on Pearl Harbor,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.78,0:22:57.91,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the United States government was looking for allies
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.92,0:22:59.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,behind the lines in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.13,0:23:02.21,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The Americans were hoping to find a way
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.22,0:23:04.92,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to undermine Japanese forces there
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.42,0:23:08.29,英文对白,,0,0,0,,when they were contacted by Ho Chi Minh.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.20,0:23:13.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And so it was decided to drop an OSS team in
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.24,0:23:15.73,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to meet with the Viet Minh leadership.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.88,0:23:20.95,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Paul Hoagland was the medic on the team.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.67,0:23:24.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And the first thing he was told was that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.26,0:23:27.28,英文对白,,0,0,0,,he must attend to their leader, who was desperately sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.94,0:23:30.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,So he was taken to a grass shack
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.19,0:23:34.98,英文对白,,0,0,0,,where a bewhiskered, skinny man lay on a bundle of straw,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.99,0:23:36.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,desperately ill.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.82,0:23:38.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And that was Ho Chi Minh.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.41,0:23:45.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The OSS, the secret wartime precursor of the CIA,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.08,0:23:48.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,supplied Ho's ragtag guerrillas with arms
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.11,0:23:52.28,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and marveled at how quickly they learned to handle them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.36,0:23:56.00,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh began to call his followers
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.01,0:23:58.26,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the "Viet-American Army,"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.43,0:24:02.26,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and praised the United States as a "champion of democracy"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.28,0:24:05.67,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that would surely help them end colonial rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.03,0:24:27.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, famine gripped the northern part of the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.37,0:24:32.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Hundreds of thousands of Vietnamese were dying of starvation
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.61,0:24:36.54,英文对白,,0,0,0,,while Japanese storehouses were filled with rice.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.02,0:24:43.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In those days, garbage was collected by people pushing carts.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.11,0:24:46.96,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And my mother remembers that every morning
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.99,0:24:50.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,she would see these garbage carts going around
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.06,0:24:53.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and people picking up dead bodies and throwing them on the cart.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.38,0:24:55.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It was incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.77,0:24:59.58,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And people who lived through it never, never forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.26,0:25:05.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Duong Van Mai's father was the deputy governor of a province east of Hanoi,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.84,0:25:10.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the son and grandson of mandarins who had all served the French.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.27,0:25:14.32,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He and his wife had 17 children.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.07,0:25:19.51,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Parents who had children who were, you know, plump,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.54,0:25:23.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were very afraid of their children being stolen and killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.60,0:25:27.70,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And it was really like hell on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.43,0:25:33.30,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The government didn't have a clue on how to deal with this calamity.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.04,0:25:36.79,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But Ho Chi Minh did.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.80,0:25:38.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He directed the Viet Minh to break
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.97,0:25:42.36,英文对白,,0,0,0,,into the Japanese storehouses wherever they could
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.37,0:25:44.98,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and distribute the rice to the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.37,0:25:49.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They were hailed as saviors.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.80,0:26:06.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,When an atomic bomb destroyed Hiroshima,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.21,0:26:11.11,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and three days later a second one destroyed Nagasaki,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.33,0:26:13.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Japanese surrender seemed imminent.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.77,0:26:19.51,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh called upon all Vietnamese to rise up
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.53,0:26:21.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and take over their own country
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.66,0:26:24.27,英文对白,,0,0,0,,before the Free French could reestablish
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.29,0:26:26.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,their old colonial regime.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.68,0:26:31.81,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They did, in cities and towns across the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.17,0:26:38.16,英文对白,,0,0,0,,On September 2, 1945,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.17,0:26:41.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the same day the Japanese formally surrendered,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.77,0:26:47.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,hundreds of thousands of Vietnamese streamed into Ba Dinh Square in Hanoi
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.26,0:26:52.17,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to see for the first time the mysterious leader of the Viet Minh
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.37,0:26:56.70,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and hear him proclaim Vietnam's independence.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.91,0:27:05.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,With an OSS officer standing nearby,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.10,0:27:09.44,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh began with the words of Thomas Jefferson:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.45,0:27:11.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"All men are created equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.01,0:27:17.55,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They are endowed by their creator with certain unalienable rights;
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.04,0:27:21.12,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that among these are life, liberty
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.53,0:27:23.63,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and the pursuit of happiness."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.06,0:27:48.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh had great hopes
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.19,0:27:53.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that the U.S. would support the Vietnam desire for independence,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.27,0:27:55.98,英文对白,,0,0,0,,not necessarily by intervening
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.24,0:27:59.27,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but by doing what it could
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.29,0:28:01.92,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to support an independence movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.98,0:28:07.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh's hopes for American support were calculated
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.10,0:28:08.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but understandable.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.03,0:28:13.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,President Franklin Roosevelt had promised a postwar world
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.78,0:28:16.67,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that would "respect the rights of all peoples
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.69,0:28:20.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to choose the form of government under which they live."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.70,0:28:24.63,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But Roosevelt was dead now,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.63,0:28:26.99,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and his successor, Harry Truman,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.01,0:28:29.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,had inherited a very different world.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.01,0:28:33.44,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The alliance with the Soviet Union that had
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.46,0:28:36.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,won the Second World War had collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.96,0:28:39.29,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The Soviets now occupied the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.30,0:28:41.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Eastern European countries they had overrun,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.24,0:28:45.00,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and hoped to spread their influence farther,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.10,0:28:48.66,英文对白,,0,0,0,,into Iran, Turkey, and the Mediterranean.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.32,0:28:53.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,A new cold war had begun.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.74,0:28:57.31,英文对白,,0,0,0,,French president Charles De Gaulle warned
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.32,0:28:59.62,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that if the United States insisted
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.62,0:29:02.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,on independence for her colonies,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.17,0:29:04.08,英文对白,,0,0,0,,France might have no choice
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.09,0:29:06.67,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but to "fall into the Russian orbit."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.42,0:29:11.14,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The United States must do nothing to undercut
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.15,0:29:14.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the restoration of France's empire,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.31,0:29:16.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,including Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.46,0:29:23.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,There were hardly any Americans in Vietnam, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.96,0:29:25.61,英文对白,,0,0,0,,State Department people,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.63,0:29:27.16,英文对白,,0,0,0,,consular officials,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.32,0:29:29.43,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a few businessmen.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.58,0:29:31.81,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Hardly anyone from this country
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.84,0:29:33.67,英文对白,,0,0,0,,knew where Vietnam was located.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.46,0:29:38.30,英文对白,,0,0,0,,George Wickes was part of a seven-man OSS mission
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.33,0:29:42.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,sent to Saigon, the largest city in the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.67,0:29:45.17,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The United States was officially neutral,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.27,0:29:47.88,英文对白,,0,0,0,,hoping the French and Viet Minh could reach
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.90,0:29:50.66,英文对白,,0,0,0,,some peaceful solution on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.63,0:29:55.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Allied leaders had agreed temporarily to divide Vietnam
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.57,0:29:57.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,into two separate zones.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.88,0:30:01.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Nationalist Chinese troops were to handle things in the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.22,0:30:06.99,英文对白,,0,0,0,,British colonial troops would try to perform the same task in the south,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.42,0:30:11.55,英文对白,,0,0,0,,where rival factions, including the French and Viet Minh,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.56,0:30:14.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were already fighting in the streets of Saigon.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.60,0:30:18.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,No one was in charge.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.97,0:30:24.29,英文对白,,0,0,0,,On both sides, there was brutality and atrocity and violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.27,0:30:26.90,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It wasn't quite a civil war
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.91,0:30:30.45,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but it was getting very close to civil war in the streets of Saigon.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.27,0:30:35.49,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Lieutenant Colonel Peter Dewey, the 28-year-old
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.50,0:30:38.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,commander of the OSS in Saigon,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.14,0:30:40.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,tried to make sense of it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.56,0:30:43.49,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Right from the start he was in touch with everybody...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.55,0:30:44.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,not only the French,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.76,0:30:47.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but very soon he established a connection with
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.59,0:30:49.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,various Vietnamese groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.17,0:30:53.02,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The Viet Minh soon established themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.04,0:30:55.02,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as the most successful.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.68,0:30:59.11,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Dewey, who spoke fluent French,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.12,0:31:02.20,英文对白,,0,0,0,,brokered talks between a Viet Minh spokesman
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.22,0:31:05.15,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and the senior French representative in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.69,0:31:10.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,His efforts infuriated British general Douglas Gracey,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.61,0:31:13.36,英文对白,,0,0,0,,who commanded Allied forces in the south.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.09,0:31:16.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Gracey was convinced that French control
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.73,0:31:19.54,英文对白,,0,0,0,,should be reimposed as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.98,0:31:22.96,英文对白,,0,0,0,,By conferring with the Viet Minh, Gracey said,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.97,0:31:26.54,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Colonel Dewey had become a "subversive" force.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.73,0:31:32.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The violence in and around Saigon escalated.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.07,0:31:37.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Colonel Dewey urgently cabled his superiors:
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.22,0:31:40.90,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Vietnam "is burning," he wrote.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.00,0:31:43.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"The French and British are finished here
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.65,0:31:49.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and the United States," he concluded, "ought to clear out of Southeast Asia."
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.64,0:31:54.15,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Two days later,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.16,0:31:57.37,英文对白,,0,0,0,,September 26, 1945,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.60,0:31:59.48,英文对白,,0,0,0,,he set out for the airport,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.72,0:32:02.85,英文对白,,0,0,0,,prepared to fly to OSS headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.87,0:32:06.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,At a roadblock,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.19,0:32:09.51,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the Viet Minh mistook Dewey for a Frenchman
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.52,0:32:10.98,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and opened fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.84,0:32:15.17,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He was killed instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.67,0:32:20.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh wrote to the United States
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.26,0:32:22.65,英文对白,,0,0,0,,lamenting the death of Dewey,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.65,0:32:24.78,英文对白,,0,0,0,,whom he recognized
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.79,0:32:27.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as a person sympathetic to his cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.07,0:32:31.61,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It seemed a terrible irony that Dewey, who was
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.13,0:32:35.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,doing what he could to help the Vietnamese independence movement
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.47,0:32:39.48,英文对白,,0,0,0,,should have been killed by the Vietnamese by a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.51,0:32:56.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,An elderly African-American woman answered the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.63,0:33:04.91,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I think she knew the instant she saw us why we were there.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.78,0:33:10.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And the padre said, uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.11,0:33:14.48,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"I'm... I'm terribly sorry to inform you,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.51,0:33:18.44,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but your son was killed in Vietnam."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.82,0:33:22.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And she just sat down. Didn't say a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.75,0:33:28.73,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Then the... her husband says, "No, there's a mistake."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.75,0:33:30.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He comes back with this letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.71,0:33:32.41,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And he said, "Look, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.95,0:33:36.51,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We got it yesterday, my... our son was still alive yesterday."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.33,0:33:41.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And the chaplain looked at the letter
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.08,0:33:42.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and he said, "It's a week old.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.40,0:33:47.07,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I think your son was killed on the day he wrote this letter."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.47,0:33:57.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In the fall of 1945,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.93,0:34:00.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a week after Colonel Dewey's death,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.24,0:34:03.50,英文对白,,0,0,0,,fresh French troops began arriving in Saigon,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.71,0:34:05.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,taking over from the British.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.05,0:34:09.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They quickly established control of the city
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.95,0:34:13.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and set out to reoccupy the entire country.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.54,0:34:19.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh hoped somehow to achieve independence
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.11,0:34:20.88,英文对白,,0,0,0,,without a war with France,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.90,0:34:24.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and he still hoped the United States would intervene.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.48,0:34:26.16,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"You never had an empire,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.24,0:34:28.78,英文对白,,0,0,0,,never exploited the Asian peoples,"
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.79,0:34:31.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,he would tell a visiting American journalist.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.66,0:34:35.49,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"Do not be blinded by this issue of communism."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.51,0:34:40.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He did not want to fight the French as an enemy of America.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.44,0:34:47.95,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And, in fact, I saw the letters he wrote to President Truman
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.51,0:34:51.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,saying, "We believe in the same things you believe."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.87,0:34:55.26,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Those letters I saw in the CIA files,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.64,0:34:59.27,英文对白,,0,0,0,,they had never been given to President Truman.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.08,0:35:06.33,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In June of 1946,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.34,0:35:08.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh returned to Paris
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.47,0:35:10.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,in a fruitless attempt to get the French
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.80,0:35:13.11,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to live up to a promise they had made
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.12,0:35:16.01,英文对白,,0,0,0,,of increased autonomy for his country.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.42,0:35:18.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,While Ho was away,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.78,0:35:21.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,General Giap began consolidating
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.18,0:35:23.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,communist control of the revolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.65,0:35:26.74,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He conducted a merciless purge of
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.76,0:35:29.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,members of rival nationalist parties
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.62,0:35:33.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and people he called "reactionary saboteurs"...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.17,0:35:36.15,英文对白,,0,0,0,,landlords and moneylenders,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.29,0:35:38.51,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Trotskyites and Catholics,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.61,0:35:42.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,men and women accused of collaborating with the French.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.90,0:35:46.92,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Hundreds were shot, drowned, buried alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.54,0:36:03.27,英文对白,,0,0,0,,On December 19, 1946,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.27,0:36:05.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,after months of building tension,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.02,0:36:10.12,英文对白,,0,0,0,,fighting broke out in Hanoi between the Viet Minh and the French.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.67,0:36:18.17,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The Viet Minh proved no match for French firepower.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.52,0:36:27.62,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho, Giap, and their comrades slipped out of the city
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.85,0:36:31.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and returned to their mountain stronghold far to the north.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.85,0:36:37.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"Those who have rifles will use their rifles,"
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.13,0:36:39.34,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho declared in a radio address
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.36,0:36:42.14,英文对白,,0,0,0,,calling for a nationwide guerrilla war.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.90,0:36:46.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"Those who have swords will use swords;
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.27,0:36:51.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,those who have no swords will use spades or sticks."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.47,0:37:24.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But the country Ho Chi Minh hoped to unite
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.58,0:37:27.16,英文对白,,0,0,0,,was itself bitterly divided.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.65,0:37:30.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Families were being torn apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.83,0:37:34.16,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Despite her father's position in the French government,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.18,0:37:39.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Duong Van Mai's sister felt compelled to answer Ho's call.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.05,0:37:45.48,英文对白,,0,0,0,,My older sister Thang was married to a man
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.49,0:37:48.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,who had great sympathy for the Viet Minh.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.40,0:37:52.00,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And by that time Ho Chi Minh had evacuated
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.03,0:37:54.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,his government to the mountain base.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.13,0:37:57.33,英文对白,,0,0,0,,So my sister and her husband trekked
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.46,0:37:59.95,英文对白,,0,0,0,,all the way from Hanoi toward the base
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.26,0:38:04.20,英文对白,,0,0,0,,in order to join the resistance against the French.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.19,0:38:08.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,So the Vietnam War was really a civil war
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.79,0:38:10.41,英文对白,,0,0,0,,down to the family level.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.87,0:38:22.33,英文对白,,0,0,0,,France poured thousands of men into Vietnam...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.08,0:38:25.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,French regulars, European mercenaries,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.96,0:38:30.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and colonial troops from Morocco, Algeria, Tunisia, and Senegal...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.49,0:38:35.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,who fought alongside an army of Cambodians,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.09,0:38:36.15,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Laotians,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.16,0:38:39.26,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and anti-communist Vietnamese.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.02,0:38:45.12,英文对白,,0,0,0,,French forces managed to occupy
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.14,0:38:48.43,英文对白,,0,0,0,,most of the large towns and province capitals
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.79,0:38:52.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and established hundreds of isolated outposts.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.14,0:38:58.62,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The French also set out to try to win over rural Vietnamese
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.63,0:39:02.08,英文对白,,0,0,0,,through a program they called pacification...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.20,0:39:03.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,pacification...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.86,0:39:06.96,英文对白,,0,0,0,,building dikes, schools and roads,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.10,0:39:09.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and vaccinating children.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.07,0:39:14.45,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The French would pacify a village
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.46,0:39:18.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and during the daytime they could control it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.72,0:39:21.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But at night the Viet Minh would come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.61,0:39:25.22,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And so it was never completely secure.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.14,0:39:29.66,英文对白,,0,0,0,,My father would shake his head and said, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.69,0:39:31.73,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"Pacification is really futile
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.75,0:39:35.81,英文对白,,0,0,0,,because it's like trying to hold sand in your fingers."
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.16,0:39:41.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The Viet Minh mined roads,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.57,0:39:43.99,英文对白,,0,0,0,,blew up bridges and railroads,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.47,0:39:47.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,ambushed French patrols,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.91,0:39:49.53,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and then disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.05,0:39:56.14,英文对白,,0,0,0,,French soldiers sometimes took revenge on the nearest village,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.16,0:39:59.02,英文对白,,0,0,0,,burning homes, raping women,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.04,0:40:03.17,英文对白,,0,0,0,,executing men suspected of aiding the Viet Minh.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.78,0:40:43.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But the communists proved
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.76,0:40:46.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,every bit as ruthless as the French.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.81,0:40:50.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"It is better to kill even those who might be innocent,"
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.37,0:40:54.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,one commander said, "than to let a guilty person go."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.21,0:40:58.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And they specifically targeted
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.25,0:41:01.29,英文对白,,0,0,0,,anyone who had links to the French.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.48,0:41:04.34,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Once my father started working for the French,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.38,0:41:06.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,then he was a target,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.04,0:41:08.16,英文对白,,0,0,0,,especially the higher he rose,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.17,0:41:10.14,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the bigger target he became.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.92,0:41:15.28,英文对白,,0,0,0,,A Viet Minh agent actually came in with a pistol
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.32,0:41:16.45,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to shoot him
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.47,0:41:19.27,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but at the last moment decided not to.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.93,0:42:01.74,英文对白,,0,0,0,,French casualties continued to mount.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.26,0:42:05.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"There are days when we are so discouraged
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.65,0:42:07.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that we would like to give it all up,"
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.86,0:42:09.95,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a French soldier wrote his mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.23,0:42:12.20,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"Convoys under attack,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.21,0:42:13.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,roads cut,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.58,0:42:16.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,firing in all directions every night,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.88,0:42:19.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the indifference at home."
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.74,0:42:32.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,While I was there I had the opportunity to call my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.05,0:42:36.43,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And I was telling my mother what was happening over there,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.45,0:42:38.45,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and I was telling her how
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.48,0:42:42.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,she shouldn't believe what she sees in the newspaper and sees on television
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.70,0:42:44.36,英文对白,,0,0,0,,because we're losing the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.26,0:42:48.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I said, "And you'll probably never see me again
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.05,0:42:50.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,because we're the most northern outpost
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.80,0:42:52.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that the Marines have, you know."
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.63,0:42:54.85,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We could literally... could look right into North Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.88,0:42:57.27,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We could see the sparks when the guns fired on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.29,0:42:59.54,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And I said, "And everybody in my unit is dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.34,0:43:01.79,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I probably won't be coming back."
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.82,0:43:03.75,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And my mother said, "No, you're coming back."
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.09,0:43:07.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,She said, "I talk to God every day and you're special.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.01,0:43:09.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,You're coming back."
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.70,0:43:12.26,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And I said, "Ma, everybody's mother
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.26,0:43:13.86,英文对白,,0,0,0,,thinks that they're special.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.09,0:43:18.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,You know, I'm putting pieces of special people in bags."
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.33,0:43:26.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,President Truman's dramatic announcement
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.06,0:43:27.49,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that Russia had the atom secret
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.53,0:43:30.88,英文对白,,0,0,0,,caused state departments all over the world to stir uneasily.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.57,0:43:36.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We were very aware that there was a Cold War
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.25,0:43:38.00,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and that we had an enemy,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.03,0:43:41.28,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and that enemy was the Soviet Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.13,0:43:45.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The United States stood at one pole
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.28,0:43:47.50,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and the Soviet Union stood at the other pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.51,0:43:50.51,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It was kind of a Manichean dynamic
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.53,0:43:52.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that there was evil and there was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.63,0:43:54.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And we were good, and the other side was evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.21,0:43:57.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It wasn't morally ambiguous.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.96,0:44:04.58,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Just a few weeks after Russia became a nuclear power,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.61,0:44:07.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,there was more stunning news...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.13,0:44:11.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,communist forces under Mao Zedong seized control of China.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.53,0:44:16.99,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Separate communist insurrections were also underway
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.03,0:44:20.70,英文对白,,0,0,0,,in the British colonies of Burma and Malaya.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.43,0:44:24.49,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In January 1950,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.51,0:44:28.63,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Mao formally recognized Ho Chi Minh's insurgency
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.65,0:44:31.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and agreed to provide the arms, equipment,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.58,0:44:34.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and military training he had been seeking.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.09,0:44:38.37,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The Soviets recognized the Viet Minh as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.41,0:44:40.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and also offered help.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.81,0:44:44.30,英文对白,,0,0,0,,President Truman, who was being blamed
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.33,0:44:47.98,英文对白,,0,0,0,,by his political opponents for having "lost" China,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.04,0:44:50.74,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and having failed to "contain" communism,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.88,0:44:54.28,英文对白,,0,0,0,,approved a $23 million aid program
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.29,0:44:56.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,for the French in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.69,0:45:01.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The United States was no longer neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.36,0:45:04.78,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We were caught on the horns of a dilemma
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.21,0:45:09.44,英文对白,,0,0,0,,of how can we maintain our friendship and our alliance with the French
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.52,0:45:11.85,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and support them in Indochina
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.97,0:45:15.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,while we, as a former colony ourselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.21,0:45:18.40,英文对白,,0,0,0,,sympathized with the Vietnamese and their aspirations
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.43,0:45:20.27,英文对白,,0,0,0,,for freedom and independence?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.87,0:45:27.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,A highly trained and well-equipped North Korean Army
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.67,0:45:30.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,swarmed across the 38th parallel to attack
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.15,0:45:32.22,英文对白,,0,0,0,,unprepared South Korean defenders.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.54,0:45:35.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In June of 1950,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.86,0:45:39.07,英文对白,,0,0,0,,China's ally, communist North Korea,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.08,0:45:41.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,invaded South Korea.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.88,0:45:45.67,英文对白,,0,0,0,,President Truman ordered tens of thousands of
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.69,0:45:49.26,英文对白,,0,0,0,,American ground troops onto the Korean Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.40,0:45:57.43,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The United States and its allies
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.45,0:46:00.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,eventually pushed the invaders back north.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.21,0:46:04.31,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile in southern China,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.34,0:46:07.79,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Mao's military was beginning to turn the Viet Minh
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.80,0:46:10.11,英文对白,,0,0,0,,into a modern fighting force,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.76,0:46:15.42,英文对白,,0,0,0,,capable of inflicting a heavy toll on the French occupiers.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.13,0:46:24.54,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In July, the Truman administration
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.55,0:46:27.01,英文对白,,0,0,0,,quietly dispatched transport planes
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.04,0:46:29.84,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and a shipload of jeeps to Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.42,0:46:33.01,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Thirty-five military advisors
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.01,0:46:35.36,英文对白,,0,0,0,,went along to oversee their use.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.10,0:46:40.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,None of them, and no one in the American embassy,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.48,0:46:43.22,英文对白,,0,0,0,,spoke a word of Vietnamese.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.20,0:46:48.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But the United States was now officially in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.84,0:46:53.27,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In October of 1950,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.30,0:46:56.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,hundreds of thousands of Chinese troops
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.26,0:46:58.55,英文对白,,0,0,0,,began pouring into North Korea,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.68,0:47:01.91,英文对白,,0,0,0,,driving the allies back down the peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.73,0:47:04.33,英文对白,,0,0,0,,As that fighting raged,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.35,0:47:07.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Truman continued to increase military aid
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.89,0:47:10.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,for the French war in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.09,0:47:16.34,英文对白,,0,0,0,,If aggression is successful in Korea,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.35,0:47:19.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,we can expect it to spread throughout Asia and Europe
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.58,0:47:21.26,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and to this hemisphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.98,0:47:25.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We are fighting in Korea
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.72,0:47:28.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,for our own national security and survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.88,0:47:37.22,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In the autumn of 1951,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.46,0:47:39.75,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a young Massachusetts congressman
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.76,0:47:41.51,英文对白,,0,0,0,,named John F. Kennedy
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.51,0:47:44.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,dined at the rooftop bar of the Hotel Majestic
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.98,0:47:46.85,英文对白,,0,0,0,,overlooking Saigon.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.69,0:47:49.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,As he and his party ate,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.56,0:47:53.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,they could hear the thunder of guns across the Saigon River.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.95,0:47:57.40,英文对白,,0,0,0,,French commanders assured Kennedy
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.41,0:47:59.95,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that with more American support,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.96,0:48:02.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,French rule would be re-established.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.23,0:48:06.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But Kennedy spent two hours with Seymour Topping,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.71,0:48:08.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a seasoned American reporter,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.92,0:48:11.50,英文对白,,0,0,0,,who gave him a very different perspective:
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.27,0:48:14.43,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the French were losing, he said,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.48,0:48:18.36,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and many Vietnamese, who had once admired the Americans,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.38,0:48:22.15,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were beginning to despise them for backing the French.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.35,0:48:25.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Kennedy believed the reporter.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.90,0:48:29.37,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Unless the United States could persuade the Vietnamese
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.39,0:48:33.08,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that it was as opposed to "injustice and inequality"
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.08,0:48:34.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as it was to communism,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.74,0:48:37.63,英文对白,,0,0,0,,he told his constituents when he got home,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.90,0:48:41.99,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the current effort would result in "foredoomed failure."
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.98,0:48:53.55,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In 1952,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.56,0:48:56.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,General Dwight Eisenhower was elected president,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.78,0:48:58.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,in part because he promised
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.47,0:49:01.16,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to take a tougher stance on communism.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.02,0:49:05.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,That year, American taxpayers
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.39,0:49:08.22,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were footing more than 30% of the bill
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.23,0:49:10.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,for the French war in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.39,0:49:12.96,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Within two years,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.99,0:49:16.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that number would rise to nearly 80%.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.55,0:49:21.73,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And many of you ask this question:
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.81,0:49:26.63,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Why is the United States spending hundreds of millions of dollars
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.04,0:49:30.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,supporting the forces of the French Union
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.89,0:49:33.73,英文对白,,0,0,0,,in the fight against communism in Indochina?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.71,0:49:36.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I think perhaps if we go over to the map here,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.95,0:49:40.29,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I can indicate to you why it is so vitally important.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.84,0:49:42.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Here's Indochina.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.12,0:49:44.79,英文对白,,0,0,0,,If Indochina falls,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.89,0:49:48.21,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Thailand is put in almost impossible position.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.52,0:49:51.29,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The same is true of Malaya with its rubber and tin.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.22,0:49:56.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Now may I say that as far as the war in Indochina is concerned,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.53,0:50:01.34,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that I was there, right on the battlefield, or close to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.54,0:50:04.17,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and it's a bloody war, and it's a bitter one.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.19,0:50:13.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,By 1953, the French had been fighting for seven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.03,0:50:17.36,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They had suffered over 100,000 casualties
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.37,0:50:20.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and failed to pacify the countryside.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.54,0:50:23.49,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Six commanders had come and gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.36,0:50:26.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, the seventh commander,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.61,0:50:29.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,General Henri Navarre, assured his countrymen
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.81,0:50:31.61,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that victory was near.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.00,0:50:34.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"Now we can see it clearly," he said,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.69,0:50:37.66,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"like the light at the end of the tunnel."
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.26,0:50:43.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, large parts of the French population
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.62,0:50:46.86,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were horrified by reports of French brutality
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.82,0:50:50.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and the widespread use of napalm...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.40,0:50:52.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,gelatinized petroleum
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.53,0:50:54.20,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that burned foliage,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.22,0:50:55.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,homes,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.40,0:50:57.12,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and human flesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.93,0:51:03.41,英文对白,,0,0,0,,When returning French troops disembarked at Marseilles,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.43,0:51:07.79,英文对白,,0,0,0,,members of the longshoremen's union pelted them with rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.29,0:51:11.27,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Parisian leftists began to call the conflict
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.29,0:51:14.34,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"La Sale Guerre"... "The Dirty War."
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.82,0:51:25.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The camera was a close-up,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.25,0:51:28.29,英文对白,,0,0,0,,was over the shoulder of this storm trooper
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.30,0:51:30.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,who had a kid by the scruff of his shirt and
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.80,0:51:32.21,英文对白,,0,0,0,,he smacks him.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.22,0:51:33.30,英文对白,,0,0,0,,People screaming...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.62,0:51:34.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,At that moment in time,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.95,0:51:38.08,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I realized that anybody who really cared for America
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.09,0:51:39.78,英文对白,,0,0,0,,was sent halfway around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.79,0:51:42.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,chasing some ghost in a jungle.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.53,0:51:45.43,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In the meantime, my country's being torn apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.27,0:51:48.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,So I saw somebody who looked like my dad
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.73,0:51:50.54,英文对白,,0,0,0,,hitting somebody who looked like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.05,0:51:52.51,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Whose side would I be on?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.40,0:52:02.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In Korea, three years of combat end
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.65,0:52:06.81,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as United Nations and communist negotiators at Panmunjom sign a truce.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.97,0:52:09.36,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In July of 1953,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.58,0:52:13.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the Korean War ended in a negotiated settlement
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.15,0:52:15.33,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and a still-divided peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.00,0:52:18.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,American policymakers saw it as proof
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.84,0:52:22.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that communism in Asia could be contained.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.90,0:52:27.17,英文对白,,0,0,0,,That fall, the French indicated their willingness
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.19,0:52:30.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to begin talks to end the fighting in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.07,0:52:33.78,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh agreed to meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.10,0:52:38.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But before the negotiators were to convene in Geneva,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.22,0:52:43.79,英文对白,,0,0,0,,each side sought to improve its position on the battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.27,0:52:48.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,General Navarre set up a fortified base
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.11,0:52:51.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,in a remote valley in northwestern Vietnam
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.15,0:52:53.12,英文对白,,0,0,0,,called Dien Bien Phu,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.12,0:52:55.61,英文对白,,0,0,0,,where he hoped to lure the Viet Minh
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.63,0:52:57.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,into a decisive battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.57,0:53:04.08,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Navarre was certain that superior French firepower and air support
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.10,0:53:07.42,英文对白,,0,0,0,,would crush any attack by the Viet Minh.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.10,0:53:11.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He and his commanders saw no need to worry about
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.05,0:53:15.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the jungle-covered hills that overlooked his 11,000 men,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.57,0:53:18.07,英文对白,,0,0,0,,dug in on the valley floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.35,0:53:22.92,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The artillery commander was so confident of victory,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.94,0:53:26.54,英文对白,,0,0,0,,he complained, "I have more guns than I need."
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.52,0:53:32.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,General Giap saw his chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.74,0:53:36.00,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"We decided to wipe out at all costs
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.03,0:53:39.84,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the whole enemy force at Dien Bien Phu," he remembered.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.91,0:53:44.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,To do it, he pulled off one of the greatest
Dialogue: 0,0:53:44.64,0:53:47.58,英文对白,,0,0,0,,logistical feats in military history...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.59,0:53:51.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a feat that would be restaged in propaganda films
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.25,0:53:54.08,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and celebrated for decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.10,0:53:58.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,A quarter of a million civilian porters...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.10,0:53:59.79,英文对白,,0,0,0,,nearly half of them women...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.81,0:54:03.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,moved everything he needed for a siege,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.05,0:54:04.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,from sacks of rice
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.83,0:54:07.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to disassembled artillery pieces,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.39,0:54:09.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,on foot through the jungle.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.36,0:54:15.17,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Giap surrounded the valley with 50,000 soldiers
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.18,0:54:17.45,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and 200 big guns,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.45,0:54:20.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,dug-in and camouflaged so well
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.49,0:54:23.15,英文对白,,0,0,0,,they could not be spotted from the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.77,0:54:30.53,英文对白,,0,0,0,,On March 13, 1954,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.57,0:54:33.28,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Viet Minh artillery on the hillsides
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.30,0:54:36.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,began raining down 50 shells a minute
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.26,0:54:39.30,英文对白,,0,0,0,,on the French troops huddled below.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.41,0:54:43.70,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The airstrip was destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.47,0:54:49.53,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The besieged troops could only be reinforced
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.56,0:54:52.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and resupplied by airdrop.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.07,0:55:00.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The French artillery commander, who had underestimated his enemy,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.15,0:55:02.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.77,0:55:06.01,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The airlift to Dien Bien Phu continues...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.04,0:55:08.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,vital men and supplies for the heroic garrison
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.42,0:55:11.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that has defied the massed Viet Minh onslaughts for over six weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.82,0:55:14.48,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Today, Dien Bien Phu is a human dam
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.51,0:55:16.12,英文对白,,0,0,0,,trying to stem the red tide
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.16,0:55:18.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that threatens to engulf Southeast Asia.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.07,0:55:21.70,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The French government begged
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.72,0:55:24.25,英文对白,,0,0,0,,President Eisenhower to intervene.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.71,0:55:26.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He refused to act
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.08,0:55:30.78,英文对白,,0,0,0,,without Congressional approval and support from European allies.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.98,0:55:32.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Britain said no
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.28,0:55:37.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and the Congress would not support unilateral action.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.57,0:55:39.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The communists under Ho Chi Minh are able to
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.84,0:55:42.08,英文对白,,0,0,0,,claim that they are fighting for independence
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.09,0:55:44.58,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and the French appear to be fighting for a maintain...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.60,0:55:46.30,英文对白,,0,0,0,,maintenance of colonial rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.31,0:55:47.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I therefore believe that
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.70,0:55:50.81,英文对白,,0,0,0,,before the United States moves in, in any degree,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.85,0:55:53.34,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that independence must be granted to the people,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.37,0:55:55.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that the people must support the struggle.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.59,0:56:00.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"I am convinced," Eisenhower confided to his diary,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.80,0:56:05.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"that no military victory is possible in this theater."
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.60,0:56:08.33,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Still, without consulting Congress,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.37,0:56:12.62,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the president had secretly sent more American transport planes,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.65,0:56:18.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,their markings painted over and flown by civilian contractors,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.10,0:56:22.98,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to help resupply the desperate French troops at Dien Bien Phu.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.38,0:56:28.99,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Everyone understood that in and of itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.01,0:56:31.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Vietnam didn't mean very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.65,0:56:34.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But they believed, I believed,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.37,0:56:36.78,英文对白,,0,0,0,,if we lost it,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.88,0:56:39.90,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that the rest of Asia would tumble to communism.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.62,0:56:44.55,英文对白,,0,0,0,,You have broader considerations that might follow
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.58,0:56:48.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,what you would call the falling domino principle.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.63,0:56:52.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,You have a row of dominoes set up,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.09,0:56:55.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and you knock over the first one,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.11,0:56:57.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and what will happen to the last one is the certainty
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.61,0:57:00.25,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that it will go over very quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.71,0:57:25.42,英文对白,,0,0,0,,On the afternoon of May 7, 1954,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.43,0:57:28.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,after 55 days of siege,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.26,0:57:33.07,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the exhausted French forces at Dien Bien Phu surrendered.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.43,0:57:40.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They had lost 8,000 men, killed, wounded, or missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.47,0:57:48.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,General Giap had lost three times as many,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.13,0:57:50.74,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but he had won a great victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.01,0:58:13.26,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Even Duong Van Mai's parents could not help but be impressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:14.10,0:58:17.32,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They were very proud that the Viet Minh had defeated
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.36,0:58:20.44,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the French, this great Western power.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.46,0:58:24.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Admiration and respect on the one hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.30,0:58:26.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but fear on the other hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.62,0:58:29.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And fear was the stronger emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.90,0:58:33.65,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"We have been caught bluffing by our enemies,"
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.66,0:58:37.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Senate Minority Leader Lyndon Johnson said.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.27,0:58:42.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"Today it is Indochina, tomorrow Asia may be in flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.49,0:58:47.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And the day after, the Western Alliance will lie in ruins."
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.76,0:58:50.71,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We should have seen it as the end of
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.71,0:58:53.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the colonial era in Southeast Asia,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.05,0:58:54.37,英文对白,,0,0,0,,which it really was.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.03,0:58:57.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But instead we saw it in Cold War terms,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.78,0:59:01.84,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and we saw it as a defeat for the free world
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.88,0:59:04.40,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that was related to the rise of China.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.82,0:59:09.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And it was a total misreading of a pivotal event,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.96,0:59:11.73,英文对白,,0,0,0,,which cost us very dearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.53,0:59:20.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The former home of the League of Nations, Geneva, Switzerland,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.53,0:59:23.50,英文对白,,0,0,0,,where East is meeting West in the international conference
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.51,0:59:26.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that may decisively affect the political future of Asia.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.46,0:59:30.51,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The day after the fall of Dien Bien Phu,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.54,0:59:33.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,diplomats from nine nations gathered in Geneva
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.99,0:59:36.31,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to settle the future of Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.92,0:59:41.55,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The talks dragged on for nearly two-and-a-half months.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.48,0:59:45.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Despite their victory,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.99,0:59:49.66,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh and General Giap could not keep fighting
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.69,0:59:53.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,without more support from China and the Soviet Union.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.92,0:59:58.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But China had lost a million men in Korea
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.58,1:00:01.62,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and did not want to become involved in another war
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.64,1:00:02.99,英文对白,,0,0,0,,along its border.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.03,1:00:08.58,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The Soviet Union was hoping to ease tensions with the West.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.87,1:00:12.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Both of Ho Chi Minh's communist patrons
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.60,1:00:15.71,英文对白,,0,0,0,,urged him to agree to a negotiated settlement,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.06,1:00:20.14,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a partition like the one that had ended the Korean War.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.20,1:00:24.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho had no option but to give in.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.66,1:00:30.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In the end, no one was satisfied.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.55,1:00:37.31,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Vietnam was temporarily to be divided at the 17th parallel.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.54,1:00:42.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The 130,000 French-led troops stationed in the North
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.21,1:00:44.16,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were to withdraw to the South,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:44.40,1:00:48.45,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and somewhere between 50,000 and 90,000 Viet Minh
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.47,1:00:50.44,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were to "re-group" to the North.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.38,1:00:55.20,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The two halves would be separated by a demilitarized zone
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.39,1:00:57.43,英文对白,,0,0,0,,until an election could be held
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.45,1:01:00.51,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to reunify North and South Vietnam,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.33,1:01:05.61,英文对白,,0,0,0,,an election everyone knew Ho Chi Minh would win.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.75,1:01:42.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We had started walking up
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.11,1:01:44.54,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and we had probably gotten about a third of the way up the hill
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.56,1:01:46.32,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and then they unleashed on us.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.07,1:01:51.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We were in the middle of this horrible shit sandwich.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.66,1:01:53.00,英文对白,,0,0,0,,That's what we called it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.02,1:02:02.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,One of the things that I learned in the war is that
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.15,1:02:04.31,英文对白,,0,0,0,,we're not the top species on the planet
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.31,1:02:05.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,because we're nice.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.93,1:02:11.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,People talk a lot about how well the military turns, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.97,1:02:14.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,kids into, you know, killing machines and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.63,1:02:17.15,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And I'll always argue that it's just finishing school.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.13,1:02:27.40,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Braving the dangers
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.40,1:02:29.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,of the open sea in tiny, rickety craft,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.82,1:02:32.26,英文对白,,0,0,0,,thousands of Roman Catholic and Buddhist faith
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.28,1:02:34.66,英文对白,,0,0,0,,have found life impossible under the communists.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.76,1:02:37.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,For them, it's freedom or nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.18,1:02:43.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Under the Geneva Accords,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.15,1:02:46.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,civilians living in either half of Vietnam
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.40,1:02:48.71,英文对白,,0,0,0,,who wanted to relocate to the other
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.73,1:02:51.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,would have 300 days to do so.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.76,1:02:55.55,英文对白,,0,0,0,,My mother and father wanted to stay
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.56,1:02:57.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and meet my sister Thang again
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.93,1:03:00.02,英文对白,,0,0,0,,because they knew Thang would come back.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.04,1:03:02.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But on the other hand they couldn't risk that.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.56,1:03:06.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They were convinced that when Ho Chi Minh
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.38,1:03:08.98,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and his government arrived in Hanoi,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.00,1:03:12.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,my father would be the first one to be killed
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.80,1:03:15.40,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and all of us would be persecuted.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.82,1:03:19.99,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And I remember the day we left.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.02,1:03:23.53,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I looked around and I thought, "I never come back here again."
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.53,1:03:27.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It was extremely traumatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.48,1:03:32.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,It was like the ground was suddenly cut from under you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.77,1:03:37.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In the end, some 900,000 refugees,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.70,1:03:41.86,英文对白,,0,0,0,,including more than half of all the Catholics living in the North,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.86,1:03:43.43,英文对白,,0,0,0,,fled to the South,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.03,1:03:47.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,many of them aboard American ships.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.97,1:03:54.61,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The United States hoped somehow to encourage the building
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.64,1:03:57.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,of a legitimate government in the South.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.07,1:04:03.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,That government was now headed by Ngo Dinh Diem.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.10,1:04:06.66,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Both a Roman Catholic and a Confucian
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.68,1:04:08.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,in a largely Buddhist country,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.88,1:04:10.79,英文对白,,0,0,0,,he was a celibate bachelor
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.79,1:04:13.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,who had once planned to be a priest.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.93,1:04:20.40,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The war for us really started when we became the partner,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.42,1:04:24.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,or I would say the victim, of President Diem.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.51,1:04:30.45,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We were going to help him turn South Vietnam into a democracy.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.78,1:04:32.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,That's what he said he wanted to do.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.26,1:04:33.34,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And we believed him.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.11,1:04:35.54,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Like Ho Chi Minh,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.56,1:04:39.24,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Diem had spent years abroad seeking support
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.27,1:04:42.50,英文对白,,0,0,0,,for his own brand of Vietnamese nationalism.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.95,1:04:44.84,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He was a veteran politician
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.86,1:04:47.28,英文对白,,0,0,0,,whose loathing for the French
Dialogue: 0,1:04:47.29,1:04:50.13,英文对白,,0,0,0,,was matched only by his hatred for the communists,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.15,1:04:51.71,英文对白,,0,0,0,,who had imprisoned him
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.71,1:04:55.68,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and buried alive his eldest brother and his nephew.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.44,1:04:59.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Diem was aloof, autocratic,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.97,1:05:03.50,英文对白,,0,0,0,,mistrustful of anyone much beyond his own family.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.00,1:05:07.35,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He also proved to be shrewd, resourceful,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.37,1:05:11.50,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and skilled at exploiting the weaknesses of his opponents.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.41,1:05:16.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But he faced a daunting task in creating a new country.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.63,1:05:22.20,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The French, who still had thousands of troops
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.21,1:05:23.88,英文对白,,0,0,0,,detested Diem.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.76,1:05:28.28,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Several provinces were under the sway of religious sects
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.30,1:05:30.21,英文对白,,0,0,0,,with armies of their own.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.90,1:05:34.86,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Tens of thousands of Viet Minh soldiers had gone north,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.89,1:05:36.98,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but several thousand cadre...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.00,1:05:40.40,英文对白,,0,0,0,,trained and dedicated Communist Party workers...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.42,1:05:45.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,had stayed behind to organize resistance in the countryside.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.49,1:05:50.58,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And Saigon itself was ruled by the Binh Xuyen,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.62,1:05:53.70,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a crime syndicate backed by the French.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.11,1:05:56.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And the French were behind the Binh Xuyen,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.61,1:05:58.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,sort of supporting them
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.32,1:06:01.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,because they didn't want Diem to succeed.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.05,1:06:03.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And that became the central contest.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.96,1:06:07.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Some in the CIA believed that
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.39,1:06:10.71,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Diem could be the savior of South Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.08,1:06:12.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Others were not so sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.16,1:06:15.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"He is a messiah without a message,"
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.40,1:06:18.17,英文对白,,0,0,0,,one diplomat reported to Washington.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.18,1:06:21.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The U.S. ambassador agreed.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.16,1:06:25.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,On April 27, 1955,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.56,1:06:28.32,英文对白,,0,0,0,,President Eisenhower decided to end
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.33,1:06:31.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,American support for Diem's regime.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.79,1:06:37.00,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But then Diem made an all-out assault
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.02,1:06:39.00,英文对白,,0,0,0,,on the Binh Xuyen syndicate.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.77,1:06:43.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Suddenly in the middle of the day
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.60,1:06:47.74,英文对白,,0,0,0,,we heard gunfire and then we saw flames
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.75,1:06:50.63,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and the neighborhood was burning.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:50.64,1:06:53.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,There are hundreds of dead and wounded on both sides
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.24,1:06:56.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as the street fighting continues for an entire week.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.36,1:06:57.42,英文对白,,0,0,0,,For the United States,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.42,1:06:59.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the situation presents a grave problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.48,1:07:04.43,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Diem finally regains control of Saigon.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.99,1:07:09.14,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In the end, Diem's forces prevailed.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.04,1:07:13.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Eisenhower now saw no option
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.87,1:07:16.00,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but to stick with Diem.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.21,1:07:20.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The French then announced their intention
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.08,1:07:23.65,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to withdraw completely from South Vietnam,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.65,1:07:27.08,英文对白,,0,0,0,,ending nearly a century of occupation.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.73,1:07:31.14,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Diem became wildly popular
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.14,1:07:35.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,because he seemed to embody the nationalist cause in the South.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.33,1:07:38.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He succeeded in getting the French
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.20,1:07:40.26,英文对白,,0,0,0,,out of Vietnam all the way.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.27,1:07:43.78,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And Ho Chi Minh had only got them out of the northern half.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.41,1:07:45.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Flush with victory,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.82,1:07:48.82,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Diem called for a referendum in the South.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.70,1:07:54.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The CIA warned him not to meddle too much with the returns.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.06,1:07:58.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But when the ballots were counted,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.05,1:08:03.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Diem claimed to have won 98.2% of the vote.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.35,1:08:08.99,英文对白,,0,0,0,,On October 26, 1955,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.00,1:08:12.42,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ngo Dinh Diem named himself the first president
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.44,1:08:15.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,of the brand-new Republic of Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.46,1:08:22.53,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The election to reunify the North and South that had been promised at Geneva
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.54,1:08:24.29,英文对白,,0,0,0,,would never be held.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.08,1:08:28.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He became our ally,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.47,1:08:30.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,or rather our master,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.70,1:08:34.11,英文对白,,0,0,0,,because the goal of preventing the communists
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.12,1:08:36.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,from taking over the South was so strong
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.61,1:08:40.96,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that we couldn't afford for him to lose.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.52,1:08:44.80,英文对白,,0,0,0,,So Diem started to boss us around.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.88,1:08:47.14,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And this was a typical relationship.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.15,1:08:49.52,英文对白,,0,0,0,,You need any ally you believe
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.53,1:08:52.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to be the centerpiece of your foreign policy.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.49,1:08:54.29,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They understand that right away.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.60,1:08:57.28,英文对白,,0,0,0,,And the tail wags the dog.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.90,1:09:03.54,英文对白,,0,0,0,,From the Far East comes a distinguished visitor.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.57,1:09:06.14,英文对白,,0,0,0,,President Ngo Dinh Diem of Vietnam is accorded
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.16,1:09:09.31,英文对白,,0,0,0,,one of President Eisenhower's rare airport greetings,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.34,1:09:12.00,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as he arrives for a four-day state visit.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.01,1:09:15.81,英文对白,,0,0,0,,President Diem, one of America's staunchest allies in Southeast Asia,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.84,1:09:18.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,will seek an increase in aid to shore up his country
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.48,1:09:20.42,英文对白,,0,0,0,,against increasing communist pressure,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.43,1:09:23.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a request to which the president lends a sympathetic ear.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.87,1:09:29.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Most politicians, Democrats as well as Republicans,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:29.79,1:09:32.01,英文对白,,0,0,0,,now seemed to share the changing views
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.03,1:09:33.86,英文对白,,0,0,0,,of Senator John F. Kennedy.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.50,1:09:37.53,英文对白,,0,0,0,,South Vietnam is "our offspring," he said.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:37.55,1:09:39.43,英文对白,,0,0,0,,"We cannot abandon it."
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.52,1:09:43.45,英文对白,,0,0,0,,If it fell, the United States would be "held responsible
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.63,1:09:47.70,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and our prestige in Asia will sink to a new low."
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.33,1:09:53.21,英文对白,,0,0,0,,There had never before been a South Vietnamese nation,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.23,1:09:55.95,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but Americans, who had rebuilt much of
Dialogue: 0,1:09:55.96,1:09:58.40,英文对白,,0,0,0,,their own country during the New Deal
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.41,1:10:00.59,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and had helped rebuild Western Europe
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.61,1:10:02.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,through the Marshall Plan,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.50,1:10:06.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were convinced they could build one nonetheless.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.24,1:10:11.39,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Eisenhower ordered scores of
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.39,1:10:14.17,英文对白,,0,0,0,,American civilians to South Vietnam,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.18,1:10:16.98,英文对白,,0,0,0,,full of plans for economic development
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.99,1:10:22.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,meant to win, he hoped, the hearts and minds of the Vietnamese people.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.92,1:10:27.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But those civilians would always
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.12,1:10:29.88,英文对白,,0,0,0,,be outnumbered by military advisors,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.89,1:10:34.63,英文对白,,0,0,0,,with orders to modernize, train, and equip Diem's forces,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.64,1:10:38.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,now called the Army of the Republic of Vietnam...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.85,1:10:39.91,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the ARVN.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.47,1:10:44.85,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Some ARVN officers found American methods
Dialogue: 0,1:10:44.87,1:10:50.42,英文对白,,0,0,0,,unsuited to the guerrilla war they expected to wage against the communists.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.63,1:10:52.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Most American military advisors
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.96,1:10:55.17,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were veterans of the war in Korea,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.53,1:10:58.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,determined to prepare South Vietnamese forces
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.88,1:11:02.74,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to slow a conventional invasion from the North.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.94,1:11:08.17,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But no one in North Vietnam
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.18,1:11:11.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,was planning a conventional invasion.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.10,1:11:15.88,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh was focused on rebuilding his country,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.89,1:11:19.36,英文对白,,0,0,0,,devastated by more than a decade of war.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.45,1:11:25.74,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The communists imposed brutal land reforms
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.77,1:11:28.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,modeled on those underway in China
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.20,1:11:32.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,with a ruthlessness that left thousands of people dead,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.32,1:11:36.37,英文对白,,0,0,0,,including not only landlords who had sided with the French,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.38,1:11:40.30,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but also many villagers who had fought with the Viet Minh.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.96,1:11:46.58,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh was still determined to reunite Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.80,1:11:51.00,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But he worried that if he took direct military action against the South,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.10,1:11:54.93,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the United States would be drawn more deeply into the struggle.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.59,1:11:57.98,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He cautioned his comrades in the South to
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.98,1:12:00.77,英文对白,,0,0,0,,put their faith in political agitation
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.78,1:12:02.60,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and avoid violence.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.61,1:12:07.91,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But that message rang hollow among
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.92,1:12:10.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,embattled Southern revolutionaries struggling
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.90,1:12:15.05,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to survive under Diem's increasingly harsh regime.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:17.80,1:12:21.40,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In a campaign he called "Denounce the Communists,"
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.41,1:12:26.18,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Diem had imprisoned tens of thousands of citizens without trial
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.46,1:12:29.94,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and ordered the executions of hundreds more.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:31.47,1:12:35.28,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Now, the communists took matters into their own hands
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.29,1:12:39.12,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and began attacking South Vietnamese officials.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.52,1:13:22.84,英文对白,,0,0,0,,As violence in South Vietnam intensified,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:22.86,1:13:25.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,new leaders emerged in Hanoi.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.19,1:13:30.34,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Ho Chi Minh would remain the face of the revolution around the world,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.91,1:13:33.08,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but he now began to share power
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.09,1:13:36.44,英文对白,,0,0,0,,with men who were growing impatient with his caution,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.25,1:13:41.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,men about whom Americans knew almost nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.99,1:13:46.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The most important proved to be a carpenter's son
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.12,1:13:50.45,英文对白,,0,0,0,,from Quang Tri province in the South named Le Duan.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.03,1:13:55.75,英文对白,,0,0,0,,He had helped found the Indochinese Communist Party,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:55.77,1:13:58.90,英文对白,,0,0,0,,survived nearly ten years in a French prison,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.00,1:14:02.31,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and proved himself a shrewd political infighter
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.32,1:14:06.07,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as he rose to become First Secretary of the party.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.51,1:14:42.28,英文对白,,0,0,0,,By 1959,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.28,1:14:44.91,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Le Duan and his hardline allies
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.92,1:14:48.81,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were gaining influence within the North Vietnamese Politburo
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.83,1:14:51.28,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and beginning to change its policy.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.60,1:14:56.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They now argued that Hanoi should do everything within its power
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.77,1:15:01.31,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to help Southern revolutionaries remove Diem by force.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:22.55,1:15:26.34,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Now, bands of 40 to 50 armed Viet Minh
Dialogue: 0,1:15:26.35,1:15:29.63,英文对白,,0,0,0,,began slipping back home into South Vietnam,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.89,1:15:33.84,英文对白,,0,0,0,,following jungle paths hacked through the Laotian mountains
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.85,1:15:38.06,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that the Americans would soon call the Ho Chi Minh Trail.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:43.62,1:15:47.30,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Violence against the Diem regime steadily accelerated.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.26,1:16:00.89,英文对白,,0,0,0,,On the evening of July 8, 1959,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.89,1:16:02.25,英文对白,,0,0,0,,at Bien Hoa,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.26,1:16:04.86,英文对白,,0,0,0,,20 miles northeast of Saigon,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.87,1:16:07.51,英文对白,,0,0,0,,six American military advisors
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.53,1:16:09.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were watching a movie in their mess hall.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.46,1:16:15.49,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Viet Minh guerrillas, who had crept silently into the compound,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.50,1:16:17.56,英文对白,,0,0,0,,opened fire through the windows.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:23.01,1:16:26.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Major Dale Buis from Pender, Nebraska,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.06,1:16:30.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and Master Sergeant Chester Ovnand from Copperas Cove, Texas,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.78,1:16:31.96,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were killed.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.92,1:16:36.32,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They were the first American soldiers
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.35,1:16:39.99,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to die from enemy fire in the Vietnam War.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.93,1:16:46.62,英文对白,,0,0,0,,We must prove all over again, to a watching world,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.63,1:16:50.16,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as we sit on a most conspicuous stage,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:50.18,1:16:54.19,英文对白,,0,0,0,,whether this nation, conceived as it is
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.20,1:17:00.90,英文对白,,0,0,0,,with its freedom of choice, its breadth of opportunity, its range of alternatives,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.92,1:17:05.09,英文对白,,0,0,0,,can compete with the single-minded advance of the communist system.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.08,1:17:08.72,英文对白,,0,0,0,,On November 8, 1960,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.72,1:17:13.54,英文对白,,0,0,0,,John Fitzgerald Kennedy was elected president of the United States.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.55,1:17:16.84,英文对白,,0,0,0,,His vice president was Senator Lyndon Johnson.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.98,1:17:21.43,英文对白,,0,0,0,,They had narrowly beaten Vice President Richard Nixon
Dialogue: 0,1:17:21.45,1:17:24.41,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and his running mate, Senator Henry Cabot Lodge.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.39,1:17:29.51,英文对白,,0,0,0,,During the campaign, both Kennedy and Nixon had
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.53,1:17:33.62,英文对白,,0,0,0,,pledged to hold the line against international communism
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.72,1:17:36.32,英文对白,,0,0,0,,wherever it seemed to be a threat.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.23,1:17:40.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But very few Americans knew or cared about
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.59,1:17:43.45,英文对白,,0,0,0,,what was going on in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:44.81,1:17:47.29,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Six weeks after Kennedy's election,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.30,1:17:50.02,英文对白,,0,0,0,,at a remote jungle village called Tan Lap
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.03,1:17:51.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,near the Cambodian border,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.31,1:17:55.46,英文对白,,0,0,0,,representatives of southern revolutionary groups
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.50,1:17:59.85,英文对白,,0,0,0,,met to form a new organization to replace the Viet Minh,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.89,1:18:03.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,dedicated to overthrowing Ngo Dinh Diem
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.07,1:18:05.98,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and ousting the foreigners supporting him.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.70,1:18:12.57,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Behind the scenes, Le Duan and his communist comrades in Hanoi
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.59,1:18:14.76,英文对白,,0,0,0,,were orchestrating everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.77,1:18:19.04,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The new organization would be called
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.06,1:18:21.38,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the National Liberation Front...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.64,1:18:23.32,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the NLF.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.98,1:18:27.47,英文对白,,0,0,0,,The armed wing of the NLF was called
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.50,1:18:30.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the People's Liberation Armed Forces,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.33,1:18:33.85,英文对白,,0,0,0,,but its enemies in Saigon and Washington preferred
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.87,1:18:35.90,英文对白,,0,0,0,,a more disparaging term.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.82,1:18:39.44,英文对白,,0,0,0,,In their eyes, the revolutionaries were
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.47,1:18:42.87,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Communist Traitors to the Vietnamese Nation...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.97,1:18:46.23,英文对白,,0,0,0,,the Viet Cong.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.90,1:19:37.30,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Let every nation know,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.34,1:19:41.97,英文对白,,0,0,0,,whether it wishes us well or ill,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.60,1:19:45.55,英文对白,,0,0,0,,that we shall pay any price,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.50,1:19:48.65,英文对白,,0,0,0,,bear any burden,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.66,1:19:51.74,英文对白,,0,0,0,,meet any hardship,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.18,1:19:54.49,英文对白,,0,0,0,,support any friend,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:54.51,1:19:57.33,英文对白,,0,0,0,,oppose any foe,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.34,1:20:00.67,英文对白,,0,0,0,,to assure the survival and the success of liberty.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.68,1:20:15.61,英文对白,,0,0,0,,For me, I'd always thought of courage
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.63,1:20:17.71,英文对白,,0,0,0,,as charging enemy bunkers
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.71,1:20:20.10,英文对白,,0,0,0,,or standing up under fire.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.76,1:20:22.95,英文对白,,0,0,0,,But just to walk,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.61,1:20:26.20,英文对白,,0,0,0,,day after day from village to village
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.23,1:20:29.83,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and through the paddies and up into the mountains,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.18,1:20:35.03,英文对白,,0,0,0,,just to get up in the morning and look out at the land
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.13,1:20:38.64,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and think, "In a few minutes I'll be walking out there
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.67,1:20:41.69,英文对白,,0,0,0,,and will my corpse be there, over there?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.21,1:20:44.30,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Will I lose a leg out there?"
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.96,1:20:48.44,英文对白,,0,0,0,,Just to walk felt incredibly brave.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:49.17,1:20:51.85,英文对白,,0,0,0,,I would sometimes look at my legs as I walked,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.88,1:20:54.02,英文对白,,0,0,0,,thinking, how am I doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.80,0:00:02.97,中文对白,,0,0,0,,本片的主要支持来自于
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.97,0:00:06.40,中文对白,,0,0,0,,良善天使社会的成员们
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.58,0:00:09.46,中文对白,,0,0,0,,包括 拉凡夫妇基金会
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.79,0:00:12.89,中文对白,,0,0,0,,布莱尔利基夫妇金会
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.63,0:00:15.43,中文对白,,0,0,0,,艾布拉姆斯夫妇基金会
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.25,0:00:17.98,中文对白,,0,0,0,,德布斯夫妇基金会
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.69,0:00:21.22,中文对白,,0,0,0,,富勒顿家族慈善基金会
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.44,0:00:23.07,中文对白,,0,0,0,,蒙特龙家族基金会
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.61,0:00:25.34,中文对白,,0,0,0,,雷斯尼克夫妇基金会
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.89,0:00:28.64,中文对白,,0,0,0,,戈尔金夫妇家族基金会
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.66,0:00:29.83,中文对白,,0,0,0,,林奇基金会
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.86,0:00:32.43,中文对白,,0,0,0,,恩里科夫妇基金会
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.52,0:00:35.01,中文对白,,0,0,0,,以及这些赞助方
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.80,0:00:38.48,中文对白,,0,0,0,,主要赞助方还有
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.49,0:00:39.89,中文对白,,0,0,0,,大卫·汉密尔顿·科赫
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.00,0:00:44.25,中文对白,,0,0,0,,布拉瓦特尼克家族基金会
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.52,0:00:47.84,中文对白,,0,0,0,,帕克基金会
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.71,0:00:51.02,中文对白,,0,0,0,,国家人文基金会
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.13,0:00:53.17,中文对白,,0,0,0,,皮尤慈善信托基金会
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.25,0:00:55.97,中文对白,,0,0,0,,奈特兄弟基金会
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.17,0:00:58.50,中文对白,,0,0,0,,安德鲁·梅隆基金会
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.74,0:01:01.27,中文对白,,0,0,0,,亚瑟·维宁·戴维斯基金会
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.34,0:01:03.60,中文对白,,0,0,0,,福特基金会正义电影
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.64,0:01:05.95,中文对白,,0,0,0,,还有公共广播公司
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.03,0:01:07.92,中文对白,,0,0,0,,以及你们这样的观众
